    "updated_at": "2016-05-31T21:30:24Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Modifiers can only be added to functions, but we could add them in the same way to a state variable which means it will be applied to its accessor function. A modifier that would solve exactly this issue is the one named after Emmy Noether:\n\n```\nmodifier noether { if (msg.value > 0) throw; _ }\n```\n\nExample of usage:\n\n```\ncontract c {\n  uint public noether x;\n}\n```\n",
